'''Madura English–Sinhala Dictionary''' ({{Lang-si|මධුර ඉංග්‍රීසි–සිංහල ශබ්දකෝෂය}}) is a free [[electronic dictionary]] service developed by Madura Kulatunga.<ref name="Sunday Observer 2015-05-17">{{cite news |last=Kodagoda |first=Anuradha |url=http://archives.sundayobserver.lk/magazine/2015/05/17/art.asp?id=/magazine/2015/05/17/pg08_0&h=&pt=t |title=Madura’s moxie |work=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)]] – Youth Observer |publisher=Associated Newspapers of Ceylon Limited |date=17 May 2015 |pages=8–9 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123055940/http://archives.sundayobserver.lk/magazine/2015/05/17/art.asp?id=/magazine/2015/05/17/pg08_0&h=&pt=t |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref><ref name="The Island 2015-05-24">{{cite news|url=http://www.island.lk/modules/modpicturegallery/gallery_pictures/143238465615.jpg |title=Madura Kulatunga, a commendable contribution |work=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)]] – Watchout |publisher=Upali Newspapers |date=24 May 2015 |page=15 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ZZj2j4Dr?url=http://www.island.lk/modules/modpicturegallery/gallery_pictures/143238465615.jpg |archivedate=26 June 2015 }}</ref> It is available as computer [[software]], an online [[website]] and an [[Android (operating system)|android]] app.<ref name="The Nation 2015-06-21">{{cite news |last=Devapriya |first=Uditha |url=http://nation.lk/online/2015/06/20/maduras-story.html |title=Madura’s story |work=[[The Nation (Sri Lanka)]] – insight |publisher=Rivira Media Corporation |date=21 June 2015 |page=i10 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729103457/http://nation.lk/online/2015/06/20/maduras-story.html |archivedate=29 July 2016 }}</ref><ref name="The Daily Mirror 2015-07-15">{{cite news |last=Wickramasinghe |first=Kamanthi |url=http://epaper.dailymirror.lk/epaper/showlink.aspx?bookmarkid=574G9XDI0YT4 |title=A humble success story Madura Kulatunga |work=[[The Daily Mirror (Sri Lanka)]] – Features |publisher=Wijeya Newspapers |date=15 July 2015 |pages=A12-A13 }}</ref> The dictionary contains over 230,000 definitions including various technical terms.<ref name="Ceylon Today 2015-07-26">{{cite news |url=http://www.ceylontoday.lk/thumb/epaper-images/50096.jpg |title=Effectively bridging the language gap |work=[[Ceylon Today]] – Hello |publisher=Ceylon Newspapers |date=26 July 2015 |page=2 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729103644/http://www.ceylontoday.lk/thumb/epaper-images/50096.jpg |archivedate=29 July 2016 }}</ref><ref name="Dinamina 2015-08-08">{{cite news|last=Karunamuni |first=Kanchana |url=http://epaper.dinamina.lk/art.asp?id=2015/08/08/pg20_3&pt=p&h= |title='මේ වෙනකොට ලක්ෂ නවයක් මධුර ශබ්දකෝෂය බාගත කරගෙන' මධුර කුලතුංග |language=Sinhala |trans-title='Up to date nine lakhs have downloaded Madura Dictionary' Madura Kulatunga |work=[[Dinamina]] – Features |publisher=Associated Newspapers of Ceylon Limited |date=8 August 2015 |page=20 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123060159/http://epaper.dinamina.lk/art.asp?id=2015/08/08/pg20_3&pt=p&h= |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref> As of 2016, the dictionary has been downloaded approximately 1,000,000<ref name="The Sunday Leader 2015-08-30">{{cite news |url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/2015/08/30/madura-kulatungas-notable-achievements/ |title=Madura Kulatunga’s Notable Achievements |work=[[The Sunday Leader]] – Weekend Leader |publisher=Leader Publications |date=30 August 2015 |page=2 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123060336/http://www.thesundayleader.lk/2015/08/30/madura-kulatungas-notable-achievements/ |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref><ref name="download.cnet.com">{{cite web |url=http://download.cnet.com/Madura-English–Sinhala-Dictionary/3000-2279_4-10571464.html |title=Madura English–Sinhala Dictionary - Free download and software reviews - CNET Download.com |work=download.cnet.com |accessdate=29 July 2016 }}</ref><ref name="play.google.com">{{cite web |url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.maduraonline |title=Madura Online – Android Apps on Google Play |work=play.google.com |accessdate=29 July 2016 }}</ref> and ranks 100th most visited sites in Sri Lanka.<ref name="Silumina 2015-09-27">{{cite news |url=http://archives.silumina.lk/epaper/art.asp?id=2015/09/27/pg39_0&pt=p&h= |title=මධුර ඉංගීසි – සිංහල ශබ්දකෝෂය නිර්මාණය කළ මධුර කුලතුංග |language=Sinhala |trans-title=Madura English–Sinhala Dictionary creator Madura Kulatunga |work=[[Silumina]] – Guru Gedara |publisher=Associated Newspapers of Ceylon Limited |date=27 September 2015 |page=39 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123060552/http://archives.silumina.lk/epaper/art.asp?id=2015/09/27/pg39_0&pt=p&h= |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref><ref name="alexa.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/maduraonline.com |title=maduraonline.com Site Overview |work=alexa.com |accessdate=29 July 2016 }}</ref> The dictionary is distributed as [[freeware]].<ref name="Sunday Times 2015-09-27">{{cite news |url=http://sundaytimes.newspaperdirect.com/epaper/showlink.aspx?bookmarkid=BH0Z2NX5EHN6 |title=The generosity of Madura Kulatunga |work=[[The Sunday Times (Sri Lanka)]] – Education Times 2 |publisher=Wijeya Newspapers |date=27 September 2015 |page=4 }}</ref><ref name="software.informer.com">{{cite web |url=http://downloads.informer.com/madhura-dictionary/ |title=Madura Dictionary – Review by Software Informer Senior editor – Tyler Vidd |work=software.informer.com |accessdate=29 July 2016 }}</ref> It was initially released on November 23, 2002.<ref name="Rajina 2015-10-02">{{cite news |url=http://www.lakbima.lk/oldpapers/rajina/2015/october/2015.10.02.pdf |format=PDF |title=ඉංගීසි භාෂාව සිංහලයට සමීප කළ "මධුර" |language=Sinhala |trans-title=English language made closer to Sinhalese by "Madura" |work=Rajina – Loka Lama Dinaya |publisher=Sumathi Newspapers (Pvt) Ltd |date=2 October 2015 |page=23 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.