==Development== Kulatunga, a [[Demographics of Sri Lanka|Sri Lankan]] [[computer engineer]],<ref name="Irudina 2015-10-18">{{cite news |last=Rathnaveil |first=Ravi |url=https://fbcdn-sphotos-g-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xat1/t31.0-8/12095295_10153624684064976_1092705915489427533_o.jpg |title=යටත්වීම වෙනුවට සටන් කිරීමෙන් උපන් මධුර ශබ්දකෝෂය |language=Sinhala |trans-title=Instead of surrender Madura Dictionary was born fighting |work=[[Irudina]] – Pitu 8 |publisher=Leader Publications |date=18 October 2015 |page=VIII }}</ref><ref name="The Sunday Leader 2015-11-01">{{cite news |url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/2015/11/01/the-story-behind-madura/ |title=The Story Behind 'Madura' |work=[[The Sunday Leader]] – Business |publisher=Leader Publications |date=1 November 2015 |page=28 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123060917/http://www.thesundayleader.lk/2015/11/01/the-story-behind-madura/ |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref> wrote a [[computer program|program]] in [[Visual Basic]] for an English–[[Sinhalese language|Sinhala]] dictionary, using the dictionary entries from the English–Sinhalese Dictionary of [[Gunapala Piyasena Malalasekera]].<ref name="RanOne FM 2015-11-13">{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k_hzp37PSIU |title=Nagena Ira Program With Madura Kulatunge (Madura English–Sinhala Dictionary Maker) 2015-11-13 |last=Wanninayaka |first=Gemunu |last2=Liyanage |first2=Dinithi |work=RanOne FM |publisher=EAP Broadcasting Company Limited |date=13 November 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729104811/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k_hzp37PSIU |archivedate=29 July 2016 }}</ref><ref name="Business LK Magazine 2016-01-01">{{cite news |url=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-fCH_V7_TVJU/WVu3Vryf3QI/AAAAAAAABy0/VKDhp35u9j4I8ab32a_n5IWR0Y1si4YZgCJoC/s0/business_lk_magazine_january-2016_page_92.jpg |title=Get the word right with Madura |work=Business LK Magazine |date=1 January 2016 |pages=92–95 }}</ref> The program was marketed from 23 November 2002.<ref name="Silumina 2016-01-24">{{cite news |last=Muthumalie |first=Aruni |url=http://archives.silumina.lk/2016/01/24/_art.asp?fn=ss1601246 |title=ගහ බලපෑම් පරදා කාටත් වැඩක් ගත හැකි On line ශබ්දකෝෂයක් තැනූ මධුර කුලතුංග |language=Sinhala |trans-title=Defeating astrology effects and developed useful online dictionary for everyone by Madura Kulatunga |work=[[Silumina]] – Sithmalyaya |publisher=Associated Newspapers of Ceylon Limited |date=24 January 2016 |page=28 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123061133/http://archives.silumina.lk/2016/01/24/_art.asp?fn=ss1601246 |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref><ref name="The Island 2016-12-11">{{cite news |url=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-3X_0bPH4Pk8/WVu4SAsUKgI/AAAAAAAABr0/ipU5iLUVHQ8qGH63EQC9pu9SU15wap2SQCJoC/s0/the_island-youth_11-december-2016_page_8-9.jpg |title=Madura Kulatunga Beyond the written word |work=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)]] – YOUth |publisher=Upali Newspapers |date=11 December 2016 |pages=8–9 }}</ref> In 2008 he started a free internet version of it, the first online English–Sinhala dictionary.<ref name="Esteem Magazine 2017-04-01">{{cite news |url=http://www.esteemprime.com/2017/05/04/madura-kulatunga-reflections-on-the-world-of-dictionaries/ |title=Madura Kulatunga Reflections on the world of dictionaries |work=Esteem Magazine |date=1 April 2017 |pages=54–56 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123061310/http://www.esteemprime.com/2017/05/04/madura-kulatunga-reflections-on-the-world-of-dictionaries/ |archivedate=23 November 2018 }}</ref><ref name="Ceylon Today 2017-06-25">{{cite news |url=http://www.ceylontoday.lk/print20170401CT20170630.php?id=24058 |title=The story of Madura |work=[[Ceylon Today]] – Hello |publisher=Ceylon Newspapers |date=25 June 2017 |page=14 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702152123/http://www.ceylontoday.lk/print20170401CT20170630.php?id=24058 |archivedate=2 July 2017 }}</ref>