{{Use DMY dates|date=April 2017}} {{EngvarB|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox martial artist | name = Wasantha Soysa | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Alexander Wasantha Wikrama de Soysa | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = [[Anuradhapura]], Sri Lanka | death_date = 24 October 2015<!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = Anuradhapura, Sri Lanka | death_cause = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | other_names = Rajarata Iron Man | residence = | nationality = | ethnicity = | height = <!-- "X cm" or "X ft Y in" (conversions are automatic) --> | weight = <!-- "X kg" or "X lb" (conversions are automatic) --> | martial_art = [[Karate]] | style = | stance = | years_active = | occupation = | university = | spouse = | children = | relatives = }}
'''Wasantha Soysa''' was a [[Karate]] [[champion]] and a [[Guinness World Records|Guinness record]] holder who has approximately twelve world records,<ref name="ti">{{Cite news|url=http://www.island.lk/2009/08/25/news18.html|title=Lankan sets World Record|last=Kuruneru|first=Percy|newspaper=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]]|accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref> including breaking twelve slabs of [[concrete]] in one blow with his head and breaking 522 clay tiles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sandbox.ceylontoday.lk/31-107527-news-detail-ninja-style-murder-of-karate-champion-guinness-book-record-holder-stabbed.html|title='Ninja style' murder of karate champion - Guinness book record holder stabbed|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]]|language=en|date=26 October 2015|accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=adaderana|title=Head strong Lankan claims record|date=2009-08-24|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gz8NR6M5eQ8|accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref> His nickname was the 'Rajarata Iron Man'. Soysa was born in [[Sri Lanka]] and later went onto become the owner of a night club in [[Anuradhapura]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dbsjeyaraj.com/dbsj/archives/43722|title=Karate Champion and Guinness Record Holder Wasantha Soysa alias ‘Rajarata Iron man’ Hacked to Death in his own Night Club in Anuradhapura|date=26 October 2015|first=D. B. S.|last=Jeyaraj|work=dbsjeyaraj.com|accessdate=18 April 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> On 24 October 2015 he was [[Murder|murdered]] at his own night club in [[Anuradhapura]] by an underworld gang.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/93465/sf-loku-arrested|title=SF Loku arrested|publisher=[[The Daily Mirror (Sri Lanka)]]|language=en|date=1 November 2015|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref>
==Early life== He was born in [[Anuradhapura]] as Alexander Wasantha Wikrama de Soysa. His father, Alfred de Soysa was a businessman who was executed in 1972 after being found guilty for the notorious Kelettewa murder case in 1960s.<ref name="tst">{{cite news | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/151101/news/the-party-that-turned-into-a-murder-spree-169930.html| title=The party that turned into a murder spree| publisher=[[The Sunday Times (Sri Lanka)]]| date=1 November 2015| accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> Soysa completed his education at [[St. Joseph's College, Anuradhapura|St. Joseph's College]] and began to learn [[martial arts]] in 1974 under renowned karate instructor D.A. Welgama. After being successful figure in his career field Soysa made his first Guinness record in 1998 by breaking 525 tiles against his body.<ref name="so1">{{cite news | url=http://archives.sundayobserver.lk/2010/03/07/spe23.asp| title=Iron man turns world class hero| publisher=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)]]| date=7 March 2010| accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> On 23 August 2009 he set a new Guinness world record by breaking 12 concrete blocks in one blow with the head.<ref name="so">{{cite news | url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/most-concrete-blocks-broken-in-a-single-stack-with-the-head| title=Most concrete blocks broken in a single stack with the head| publisher=www.guinnessworldrecords.com| date=23 August 2009| accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> The previous record was held by a [[Norway|Norwegian]] national, Narve Laeret, who had broken 7 concrete blocks in 2008.<ref name="ti"/>
==Death== On 24 October 2015 Wasantha Zoysa and 3 other employees were attacked at his own night club in Kadapanaha area, Anuradhapura by a group of about 20 individuals. He was admitted to hospital with serious injuries but died the same day.<ref name="am">{{cite web | url=http://www.asianmirror.lk/news/item/12467-eight-individuals-arrested-for-anuradhapura-night-club-attack| title=Eight Individuals Arrested For Anuradhapura Night Club Attack| publisher=www.asianmirror.lk| date=26 October 2015| accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> He was 57 years old at the time of his death.<ref name="hn">{{cite news | url=http://www.hirunews.lk/119089/suspects-in-killing-anuradhapura-night-club-owner-identified| title=Suspects in killing anuradhapura night club owner identified| publisher=www.hirunews.lk| date=26 October 2015| accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref>
